<section
  class="border-y border-border bg-[color-mix(in_oklab,var(--color-panel)_55%,var(--color-bg))] py-[clamp(56px,9vw,80px)]"
>
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow reveal">The feeling target</span>
    <h2
      class="reveal mt-4 max-w-[20ch] text-[clamp(30px,4.4vw,56px)] leading-[1.0] tracking-[-0.03em]"
    >
      A living system with the restraint of an operator tool.
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-[44px] grid grid-cols-1 gap-[28px] md:grid-cols-3 md:gap-[clamp(24px,4vw,48px)]">
      <div
        class="tword reveal border-t-2 border-fg pt-[18px] text-[clamp(22px,2.4vw,30px)] tracking-[-0.02em]"
      >
        Alive<span class="mt-3 block text-[15px] leading-[1.5] tracking-normal text-muted"
          >Every bit of motion or color reports real agent state — thinking, running, blocked, done. If it isn't conveying work, it doesn't belong.</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="tword reveal border-t-2 border-fg pt-[18px] text-[clamp(22px,2.4vw,30px)] tracking-[-0.02em]"
      >
        Composed<span class="mt-3 block text-[15px] leading-[1.5] tracking-normal text-muted"
          >Day-to-day surfaces stay quiet, dense and consistent. Expressive treatment is reserved for a few earned thresholds, never sprinkled around.</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="tword reveal border-t-2 border-fg pt-[18px] text-[clamp(22px,2.4vw,30px)] tracking-[-0.02em]"
      >
        Precise<span class="mt-3 block text-[15px] leading-[1.5] tracking-normal text-muted"
          >Direct and technical. No hype, no cute. Commanding a fleet from a quiet, well-instrumented deck where you can see everything and nothing is shouting.</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
